The paper focuses on improving the performance predictability of cloud microservices, which falls under the category of distributed computing (cs.DC). The paper also leverages deep learning (cs.NE) to analyze the massive amount of tracing data collected by cloud systems. Additionally, the paper discusses the design and architecture of microservices (cs.SE), and proposes a system for online performance debugging (cs.SY). Finally, the paper evaluates the proposed system using real-world deployments, which involves analyzing and interpreting data (cs.DL).
